headline: How New US Chip Production Rules Could Impact Texas Instruments Valuation
summary: Wondering whether it's the right moment to jump into Texas Instruments stock, or perhaps time to hold back? You're not alone. With chipmakers like TI front and center in the latest geopolitical and trade headlines, investors are watching every move. Over the last year, TI's share price has dipped by 13.8%, with the last month alone seeing a 6.9% drop. Yet, when you zoom out to the three- and five-year marks, the stock is still up 26.6% and 29.0% respectively, which hints at underlying staying...
